    "Dr. Peter S. Ruckman": "says \u201cfully persuaded that, what he had promised, he was able also to perform.\u201d So as faith grows, doubt dies, until faith has no doubt at all about the promise of God. Now, this is important concerning salvation. A weak faith can save anyone. But if you want to grow in your Christian life and have victory, then you have to go beyond a weak faith. Otherwise you will be stumbling through life hoping you are saved, thinking you are saved, trying to \u201clive it\u201d to get saved, and never do anything of consequence for God. If there is anything about which a Christian ought to have a strong faith, it is salvation. The Apostle John `[char_John_Ref]` says you can know that you have eternal life (1 John `[char_John_Ref]` 5:13). I\u2019ll ask you what Hugh Pyle, the man who led me to Christ, asked me after I prayed to accept Christ in the record room of WEAR in downtown Pensacola: \u201cDo you know or don\u2019t you?\u201d You say, \u201cI accepted Christ, and I still don\u2019t know for sure.\u201d Then get like Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]`. Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]` said, \u201cI am PERSUADED\u201d that nothing \u201cshall be able to separate us from the love of God, which is in Christ Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` our Lord\u201d (Rom. 8:38\u201339). He said, \u201cFor I know whom I have believed, and am PERSUADED that he is able to keep that which I have committed unto him against that day\u201d (2 Tim. 1:12). Back in the old days when a man was asked to what church he belonged, the question was, \u201cWhat is your persuasion?\u201d They didn\u2019t use the word denomination . When D. L. Moody was asked that, he replied, \u201cMy persuasion is Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]`\u2019s persuasion.\u201d He was asked, \u201cWhat\u2019s that?\u201d He said, \u201cI...am persuaded that he is able to keep that which I have committed unto him against that day.\u201d If you know that you trusted Christ and yet don\u2019t know for sure that you\u2019re saved, then get your nose in the Scriptures and find the promises until you are persuaded that your salvation is so. When that is settled, you can go on and do something worthwhile for God. Now, when it comes to faith, do you know what our problem is? We are able to trust God in general terms, but when it comes to the specifics , that\u2019s where we have the problem. \u201cThe devil is in the details,\u201d as the saying goes. Take Abraham `[char_Abraham_Exo_17]`, for an example. Look at\nVerse 21 says \u201cfully persuaded that, what he had promised, he was able also to perform.\u201d So as faith grows, doubt dies, until faith has no doubt at all about the promise of God. Now, this is important concerning salvation. A weak faith can save anyone. But if you want to grow in your Christian life and have victory, then you have to go beyond a weak faith. Otherwise you will be stumbling through life hoping you are saved, thinking you are saved, trying to \u201clive it\u201d to get saved, and never do anything of consequence for God. If there is anything about which a Christian ought to have a strong faith, it is salvation. The Apostle John `[char_John_Ref]` says [v_1Jn_5_13] you can know that you have eternal life (1 John `[char_John_Ref]` 5:13). I\u2019ll ask you what Hugh Pyle, the man who led me to Christ, asked me after I prayed to accept Christ in the record room of WEAR in downtown Pensacola: \u201cDo you know or don\u2019t you?\u201d You say, \u201cI accepted Christ, and I still don\u2019t know for sure.\u201d Then get like Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]`. Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]` said, \u201cI am PERSUADED\u201d that nothing \u201cshall be able to separate us from the love of God, [v_Rom_8_38] which is in Christ Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` our Lord\u201d (Rom. 8:38\u201339). He said, \u201cFor I know whom I have believed, and am PERSUADED that he is able to keep that which I have committed unto him against [v_2Ti_1_12] that day\u201d (2 Tim. 1:12). Back in the old days when a man was asked to what church he belonged, the question was, \u201cWhat is your persuasion?\u201d They didn\u2019t use the word denomination. When D. L. Moody was asked that, he replied, \u201cMy persuasion is Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]`\u2019s persuasion.\u201d He was asked, \u201cWhat\u2019s that?\u201d He said, \u201cI...am persuaded that he is able to keep that which I have committed unto him against that day.\u201d If you know that you trusted Christ and yet don\u2019t know for sure that you\u2019re saved, then get your nose in the Scriptures and find the promises until you are persuaded that your salvation is so. When that is settled, you can go on and do something worthwhile for God. Now, when it comes to faith, do you know what our problem is? We are able to trust God in general terms, but when it comes to the specifics, that\u2019s where we have the problem. \u201cThe devil is in the details,\u201d as the saying goes. Take Abraham `[char_Abraham_Exo_17]`, for an example. Look at",
