    "Commentary Vol. 83": "So went the present over before him, etc.] Over the brook Jabbok `[place_Jabbok_Gen_32]`, after mentioned, the night before Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]` did: and himself lodged that night in the company; or \u201cin the camp\u201d f1537, either in the place called Mahanaim, from the hosts or crowds of angels seen there; or rather in his own camp, his family and servants; or, as Aben Ezra distinguishes, in the camp with his servants, and not in his tent, lest his brother should come and smite him; and so Nachmanides.\nVer."
